{"lemma":"سُبَحُ","slug":"سُبَحُ","root":"س.ب.ح","root_slug":"س-ب-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سُبَحُ","root":"سبح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18662"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"misbaha, rosary"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sub.ħa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18662","headword_ar":"سَبَحَ","root":"sbH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHN","text_ar":"سَبْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAHapN","text_ar":"سِبَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He swam,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAma","text_ar":"عَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~ahori","text_ar":"بِالنَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the river"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmaA='i","text_ar":"بِالمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY AlmaA='i","text_ar":"فى المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for it is likewise in the sea, and in a pool, and also in any expanse: (MF, TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he swam upon the surface, without immersing himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for,] accord. to Z, there is a difference between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawomN","text_ar":"عَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAHapN","text_ar":"سِبَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the former signifying the “ coursing along in water with immersion of oneself; ” and the latter, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coursing along upon water without immersion of oneself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ujuwmu tasobaHu","text_ar":"النُّجُومُ تَسْبَحُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alfalaki","text_ar":"فِى الفَلَكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glide along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pass along, in the firmament, with a spreading forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in the Kur xxi. 34 and xxxvi. 40, with reference to the sun and the moon, (Bd and Jel in xxi. 34,) with which the stars are meant to be included, (Jel ibid.,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~N fiY falakK yasobaHuwna","text_ar":"كُلٌّ فِى فَلَكٍ يَسْبَحُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"All"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glide"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travel along swiftly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a firmament,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the swimmer"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel ibid.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the surface of the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ibid.,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel ibid.;) wherefore the form of the verb used is that which is appropriate to rational beings, (Bd and Jel ibid.,) swimming being the act of such beings. (Bd ibid.) ―         -b3-  And [hence] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa *ikoruka","text_ar":"سَبَحَ ذِكْرُكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosi wa Alqamari","text_ar":"الشَّمْسِ وَ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAbiHa","text_ar":"مَسَابِحَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thy fame has travelled as far as the sun and the moon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swum along the tracts along which swim the sun and the moon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b4-  [Hence, likewise, as inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa","text_ar":"سَبَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHN","text_ar":"سَبْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse (S, L, K, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the fore legs are stretched forth well"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like as are the arms of a man in swimming"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L, K, * TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming, remote."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF.) ―         -b7-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelling far."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa","text_ar":"سَبَحَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelled, far, in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into, the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"country:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaxa","text_ar":"سَبَخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": both thus expl. by Abu-l-Jahm El-Jaafaree. (TA.) ―         -b8-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"journeying for the purpose of traffic"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqal~ub","text_ar":"تَقَلُّب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]); and [a people's]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becoming scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, in the land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"busying oneself in going to and fro,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking gain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupying oneself according to his own judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discretion, in the disposal"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"management of affairs, in respect of the means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yasobaHu Aln~ahaAra","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَسْبَحُ النَّهَارَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~ahu fiY Talabi AlmaEaA$i","text_ar":"كُلَّهُ فِى طَلَبِ المَعَاشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one busies himself in going to and fro,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupies himself according to his own judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discretion, in seeking the means of subsistence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa fiY HawaAy^ijihi","text_ar":"سَبَحَ فِى حَوَايِجِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He occupied himself according to his own judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discretion in the accomplishment of his needful affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b9-  As used in the Kur [lxxiii. 7], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a laka fiY Aln~ahaAri saboHFA TawiylFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ لَكَ فِى النَّهَارِ سَبْحًا طَوِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is variously explained: (S, TA:) accord. to Katádeh (S) and El-Muärrij, (S, TA,) the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thou hast in the day-time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long freedom from occupation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA;) and in this sense, also, its verb is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa","text_ar":"سَبَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":": (JM:) [thus it has two contr. significations:] or, accord. to Lth, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leisure for sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) accord. to AO, the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long-continued scope,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"room, for free action;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaqal~abFA TawiylFA","text_ar":"مُتَقَلَّبًا طَوِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and accord. to ElMuärrij, it means also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coming and going:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) accord. to Fr, the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou hast in the day-time the accomplishment of thy needful affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the meaning is, (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupation of thyself in thy affairs of business;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not being free from occupation therein for the reciting of the Kur-án. (Jel.) Some read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboxFA","text_ar":"سَبْخًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has nearly the same meaning as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHFA","text_ar":"سَبْحًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Zj, TA.) ―         -b10-  As inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa","text_ar":"سَبَحَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK,) it signifies also (assumed tropical:)  The state of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sleeping."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And as such also, (TK,) (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being still, quiet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b11-  [Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glistening"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the mirage.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa Als~araAbu","text_ar":"سَبَحَ السَّرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=lu","text_ar":"الا=لُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamaEa","text_ar":"لَمَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mirage glistened"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.) ―         -b12-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"digging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burrowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the earth, or ground. (K, * TA.) You say of the jerboa,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa fiY AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"سَبَحَ فِى الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dug,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burrowed, in the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b13-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being profuse"},{"kind":"text","text":"in speech. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaHa fiY AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"سَبَحَ فِى الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was profuse in speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b14-  See also the next paragraph. in two places."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","MF","TA","A","O","IAar","S","JM","TK"]}]}}